Morning Sessions SSB Symposium 8:30 - noon: Unified Approaches for Understanding Patterns of Character Evolution and Diversification  Stacey Smith (U. of Nebraska-Lincoln) and Boris Igic (U.of Illinois-Chicago) - &ldquo;Introduction to models of character state-dependent diversification&rdquo;  Introduces the BiSSE model.
 Richard Fitzjohn (U. of British Columbia) - &ldquo;Stochastic mapping incorporating differential diversification&rdquo;  BiSSE comparison to traditional discrete-trait transition rate which ignores the correlation.
 Folmer Bokma (Umeå University) - &ldquo;Estimating speciation and extinction with incomplete phylogenies&rdquo;   Emma Goldberg (University of Illinois-Chicago) - &ldquo;Modes of speciation and character change from phylogenetic trees&rdquo;

